Class AStar<T extends CostObject<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • AStar<T>

  • public class AStar<T extends CostObject<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    The A* Algorithm Class. Implements a beam search A* algorithm, which means that the OpenSet can contain a fixed amount of States.
    Classes used:
    • TreeMap which keeps results in ascending order of cost.
    • PrioQueue which serves as the OpenSet.
    • HashSet which keeps the all the visited States (pulled from OpenSet).
    • HashMap which keeps for each State its best gScore.
    See Also:
    PrioQueue, The objects that the A* can work on are based on the CostObject interface. These are objects which have some kind of method to compute the cost from one object to another.

      • solve

        public java.util.Map<Graph.Vertex<T>,java.util.List<Graph.Vertex<T>>> solve(Graph<T> graph,
                                                                            java.lang.String arg)
        The A* Algorithm implementation method. The A* Algorithm works as follows:
        • Get taxi.
        • Place it in PrioQueue with 0 gScore and its heuristic cost.
        • While OpenSet (PrioQueue) not empty do:
          • Pull first State from OpenSet.
          • If it is the client coordinates put result in TreeMap.
          • Else find neighbors.
          • Check if neighbors are visited.
          • If a neighbor is visited do nothing.
          • Else check the previous gScore of the neighbor.
          • If there is no score place currentScore in gScore and put him in the OpenSet.
          • Else check if currentScore is better than old gScore and act accordingly.
        Parameters:
        graph - The Graph which contains nodes, taxis, neighbors and client.
        arg - The capacity of the A* openSet.
        Returns:
        A TreeMap with Vertex as key and list of Vertex as value.
